cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for weakly supervised segmentation using a deep neural network with discrete constraints and regularization priors. The paper focuses on medical image segmentation, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The method is based on the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) algorithm, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of size constraints and boundary length regularization, which are common regularization techniques in computer vision and machine learning (cs.AI). The method involves training a deep neural network, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a benchmark dataset, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
